The paper deals with error rates and learning algorithms, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses sample complexity and active learning, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of classification noise is relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
